 jobs, entertainment-particularly television programs-and their social interactions with peers, employers, and others. Talking at Trena's provides a window into the laughs, complaints, experiences, and strategies which Trena's regulars share for managing daily life outside the safety and comfort of the tavern.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aAfrican AmericansxAttitudes. 0aAfrican AmericansxRace identity. 0aAfrican AmericansxSocial life and customs. 0aBars (Drinking establishments)zIllinoiszChicago. 0aMiddle classzUnited StatesxAttitudes. 0aMiddle classzUnited StatesxSocial life and customs. 0aRacismzUnited StatesxPsychological aspectsvCase studies. 0aSocial interactionzUnited StatesvCase studies. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertNew York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831107064440 cprintz978081475671340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780814739198423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780814739198/original  a978-3-11-070644-4  New York University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK